<HEADLINE> Small Plane Crashes in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A small plane crashed Tuesday in
Guayaquil, western Ecuador, but the authorities have not yet made
public the number of victims.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 09:40 a.m., and the cause of the crash
is unknown, but according to the authorities, the plane was
covered in flames.
</P>
<P>
It seems six people were in the plane, which crashed close to a
trade center north of Guayaquil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
