<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Allocates 55 Million Dollars for Cooling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Tuesday released 55 million U.S. dollars in federal aid to help
residents of nine Southern and Midwestern states cope with the
heat.
</P>
<P>
The money, provided under a program that is used more often to
help low-income people pay for heat during the winter, may be used
to buy air conditioners, fans and other relief.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made as Clinton flew to Chicago City,
where he planned to visit workers providing services to some of
the most vulnerable people suffering from the heat.
</P>
<P>
At least 221 people have died in 20 U.S. states including
Illinois and Missouri as a result of oppressively hot
temperatures since July 19. In Illinois alone, 99 deaths have been
attributed to the heat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
