minister with whom he discussed the latest developments in the
peace process and the obstacles faced by the Palestinians
concerning the implementation of Wye memorandum.
</P>
<P>
On her part, the Finnish minister, whose country is the
rotating president of the EU, stressed the importance of carrying
out the Wye accord.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the EU support to the Palestinian people and the
peace process, the minister said she hopes the process will make
further progress.
</P>
<P>
Halonen left Gaza this afternoon after visit. 
