posts, including Minister of Finance Paul Martin, Minister of
Health Allan Rock, Minister of Foreign Affairs Lloyd Axworthy,
Minister of Transport David Collenette, Minister of Justice Anne
Mclellan and Minister of Industry John Manley.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle was reported by the local media to be a signal
that Prime Minister Jean Chretien has no plans to retire any time
soon. Rather, he is intent on revitalizing his government with a
bold new team and a more inspirational vision to lead the country
into the new millennium. 
</P>
