<HEADLINE> U.S. Offers Emergency Food Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is to receive more
food aid from the United States, a press statement by the U.S.
embassy said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 90,000 metric tons of food assistance were to be provided
in response to the shortage of food in Ethiopia, which brings the
total American food aid contribution to the country so far this
year to more than 250,000 tons, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The food aid includes 10,000 tons of food assistance to replace
 previous food aid which was lost at the Port of Assab following
the onset of the Ethiopia-Eritrea border conflict.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that drought and unfavorable climate since
early this year had severely affected household food security in
many parts of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the U.S., Ethiopia has also received in the past
few months relief fund from Holland, Japan, China and Canada.
</P>
