<HEADLINE> Ugandan Govt Urged to Boost Business Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government has been
urged to streamline the legal framework to enable the business
sector to function properly.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by President of Uganda National Chamber of
Commerce, Trade and Industry, Bonney Katatumba, in the Parliament
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Long process of acquiring visas is hindering foreign investors
from coming to Uganda and freight charges ought to be removed to
reduce the cost of imports, he was petitioning the committee on
tourism, trade and industry.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Chamber representing the business expressed
concern about multi-national corporations like oil companies that
are hindering liberalization by forming cartels to limit other
countries from dealing in oil.
</P>
<P>
They appealed to the government to allocate specific areas fro
petty traders to carry out their businesses in an organized manner
in order to broaden the tax base. 
</P>
