<HEADLINE> France Backs British Candidate for NATO Top Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- France said on Tuesday that it
backs the candidacy of British Defense Secretary George Robertson
for the post of secretary general of NATO.
</P>
<P>
``France supports the candidacy of Mr. Robertson. The United
Kingdom is one of our major partners in the definition of a
European defense in the framework of the European Union (EU), in
the spirit of Saint-Malo,'' said French Foreign Ministry spokesman
Francois Rivasseau.
</P>
<P>
France and Britain agreed in November 1998 to establish a
single European defense force at a summit between President
Jacques Chirac, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin and Prime Minister
Tony Blair in Saint-Malo, northwest France.
</P>
<P>
The other member countries of the EU also expressed their
support to the Franco-British proposal at the EU summit in
Cologne, Germany, in early June.
</P>
<P>
Robertson is expected to be formally designated by the NATO
member countries' ministerial council this week to replace Javier
Solana. 
</P>
