<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Foreign Exchange Reserves Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The South African Reserve
Bank's provisional gross gold and foreign exchange reserves
amounted to 35.7 billion rand (5.76 billion U.S. dollars) at the
end of July, compared with 35.1 billion rand at the end of June,
the central bank said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In U.S. dollar terms, gross reserves were virtually unchanged
at 5.8 billion dollars owing to the devaluation of the rand over
the month.
</P>
<P>
However, the use of foreign credit lines fell by about 200
million dollars to 2.5 billion dollars (15.2 billion rand),
boosting net reserves by a matching amount to 3.3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of foreign credit lines at the end of June was
16 billion rand. 
</P>
