<HEADLINE> China Develops Military Numerical Weather Forecast System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have developed
software for a military numerical weather forecast system with the
help of high-performance computers.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the system could provide meteorological
services for local wars under high-tech conditions, as well as for
choosing suitable times for satellite launchings and military
operations.
</P>
<P>
They said the operation of the system indicates a major
breakthrough in meteorological backup for the People's Liberation
Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Based on high-performance computers and high-speed regional
networks, the numerical weather forecast system collects and
process global meteorological observation data around the clock
and provide medium-term weather forecasts.
</P>
<P>
The system was jointly developed by military scientists from
the Headquarters of the General Staff, China Meteorological Bureau,
Chinese Academy of Sciences and some other units over three years.
</P>
<P>
The system has played an important role in meteorological
backup for military operations and satellite launchings during its
trial operation period, the experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
