<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian and Cypriot
environment ministers met here Wednesday to discuss ways to tackle
the water shortage issue which they described as "acute."
</P>
<P>
"We are facing almost the same problem, like the problem of
water shortage," said Yousef Abu Safieh, visiting Environment
Minister of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA), while
meeting with Cyprus Agriculture, Natural Resources and Environment
Minister Costas Themistocleous.
</P>
