<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks End Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks ended
marginally down Wednesday as market players remained cautious to
take new positions amid confusion about the power tariff dispute
between Hub Power Company (Hubco) and the government.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index fell 3.85 points, or 0.30 percent, to
1,262.86 points from Tuesday's 1,266.71 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume traded stood at 144.575 million shares on Wednesday
against 130.611 million shares the previous day.
</P>
<P>
"There was buying interest in the market, but unless the talks
between the Water and Power Development Authority and Hubco
officials starts, the market will move in narrow range," said
Shakeel Anwar Kamal, a dealer with Prudential Securities Pvt. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Hubco, the largest private sector power producing company with
a weightage of 18 percent of the 100-share index, fell by 0.45
rupee to 21.45 rupees from 21.90 rupees on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 185 active issues, gainers managed to beat losers 72
to 60 while 53 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
