<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive at Ceremony of Youth Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hua Wednesday
met here with a delegation of overseas Chinese students from all
parts of the world who will visit the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
Tung officiated at the Commissioning Ceremony of the China
Synergy Program for Outstanding Youth and presented badges to the
youth representatives at the Government House Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The move is to provide an opportunity for outstanding Chinese
youths who are residing overseas and in Hong Kong to know more
about the socio-economic and cultural development of China.
</P>
<P>
In the two-week program of exploration and exchange activities,
the youths are expected to meet with top government officials in
Hong Kong, Shanghai, Beijing and Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
They will also tour major socio-economic and cultural
development projects, participate in exchange activities with
local undergraduates and visit local households.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is formed by some 70 outstanding undergraduates
from Australia, Canada, the United States, United Kingdom and Hong
Kong. 
