<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forestry Police Headquarters Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The headquarters of a division of
China's armed police force specially trained to fight forest fires
was established here today, in accordance with a decision by the
State Council and the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
As part of the Chinese People's Armed Police Force, the forest
police shoulder the responsibility of preventing and extinguishing
forest fires, as well as protecting forest resources.
</P>
<P>
The forestry police are mainly stationed in northeast China's
Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces, the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region and southwest China's Yunnan Province, to safeguard more
than 36.8 million ha of forest and 22 million ha of grassland.
They are also responsible for ensuring public security in forest
areas.
</P>
<P>
Although functional for 50 years, the forestry police did not
have a headquarters until this February, when the State Council
and the Central Military Commission decided to introduce a new
administrative system for the force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
