<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Life, Health, Inviolate Citizen Rights: Xinhua Commentary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A Xinhua News Agency commentary
says today that Li Hongzhi and his Falun Gong cult used people's
desire for health to spread superstition, and disturbed people's
ideas by claiming that Falun Dafa is the only way to avoid
calamity.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that from the uncovered facts, people
should have a clear understanding of the Falun Gong cult, which
defrauded practitioners and inveigled them into extremities.
</P>
<P>
"Life is the most precious thing for people, and health is the
guarantor of life," according to the commentary. Citizens have the
right to ask for help from the government and from other people.
</P>
<P>
The Party and the government always pay great attention to the
health of people, and also sets health as a key goal to be
achieved by socialism.
</P>
<P>
Since the People's Republic of China was founded in 1949, the
average life-span in the country has been raised from 35 to 70,
and the infant mortality rate has been decreased from 20 percent
to 31.4 per 1,000 births.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi and his Falun Gong cult took the opposite way and
said that disease is a "preexisting sin." He misled the Falun
Gong practitioners to superstition, and asked them to refuse to go
to the hospital. What he did severely infringed on the life and
health rights of the Falun Gong practitioners.
</P>
<P>
China has explicit laws protecting the health rights of
citizens. Li Hongzhi, however, performed a spiritual poisoning
act to lead Falun Gong practitioners into a dead end. He is the
real culprit.
</P>
<P>
The commentary calls on people to arm themselves with science
and leave no room for Li Hongzhi and other cultists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
