<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Discarded by Former Practitioners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Many former practitioners say
that Falun Gong's claim to heal the sick is false, and vow never
again to have anything to do with the cult.
</P>
<P>
Gao Qingyin, deputy chief of the Falun Gong general
instruction station in the east China province of Anhui, revealed
that one fellow practitioner suffered from a brain hemorrhage in
the second half of 1994, and died soon after.
</P>
<P>
"During his illness, we called on the Falun Dafa Research
Society four times and asked for the help of Li Hongzhi," Gao said.
However, Li, the founder of Falun Gong, did nothing.
</P>
<P>
"Li's claim that one will be well with a single wave of hand
is nothing but cheating and tricks," said Gao, who broke from the
cult when the government banned it last month.
</P>
<P>
Wang Dequn, a professor of Chinese medicine in Anhui, also
woke up. "I should never have practiced Falun Gong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Professor Wang picked up Falun Gong in 1994 when he was
engaged in some very difficult medical research. The mysterious
part of Falun Gong attracted Wang, who hoped to find some answers
in it.
</P>
<P>
However, once he joined the cult, he found himself totally
distracted from his work and medical research. "It's really
terrifying when I think of those days," he said.
</P>
<P>
University graduate Wang Weili in the city of Harbin, the
capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, attempted
suicide after she had been practicing Falun Gong for some time. "I
was ruined by Li Hongzhi and his Falun Gong cult," she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
