<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vancouver Hit By Lightening Storm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Canada's west coast city Vancouver
suffered a thousand lightening strikes Tuesday, with power outages
and a dozen forest fires reported during the storm.
</P>
<P>
Two main transmission lines to Vancouver Island from the
mainland were struck, knocking out electricity to much of the
island, as well as to several thousand homes elsewhere in the
Vancouver area, the local television said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Crews were called in to fight a dozen or so forest fires
sparked by the lightening storm, while helicopters were out
looking for any other signs of smoke, the local forest service was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
A woman doing greens maintenance at a golf course in suburban
Burnaby was injured by a lightning strike six meters away. She
was taken to hospital after being knocked off a riding mower.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the storm appeared to be bypassing when it
veered suddenly, touching down on the golf course, where staff
didn't "have a chance" for quick evacuation.
</P>
<P>
Vancouver Island was already stormed Monday night, when the
islanders counted as many as 6,000 lightening strikes, according
to the television report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
