<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chengdu-Baoji Railway Line Resumes Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The railway line from this
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province to Baoji in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province resumed operation at 7:00 p.m.
yesterday, after having been closed for 14 hours because of a
landslide triggered by torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
The slide happened at 5:00 a.m. yesterday. The section of the
railway line in Jiangyou City was covered by a pile of mud and
rocks measuring 50 m by 20 m and totaling 1,500 cu m, trapping a
passenger train.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been caused.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the accident, railway departments sent
hundreds of rescue workers to the scene. Ninety minutes later,
down trains resumed operations, and later the way was cleared for
up trains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
