<HEADLINE> Yangtze Water Level Continues to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The water level on the Yangtze
River continues to drop, with the water level of the river near
this capital of central China's Hubei Province falling below the
warning line.
</P>
<P>
The water level here had been above the warning line for one
month, and the 30-day floods have been only eight percent smaller
compared to the same period in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Being a major flood-threatened city on the Yangtze, Wuhan has
invested 650 million Yuan (about 80 million U.S. dollars) in the
construction of dams and dikes.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the upper reaches of the river have received less
rainfall during the past week, and the water levels at all the
Yangtze monitoring stations are falling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
