<HEADLINE> Large Power Transmission Plant Opens in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A 500-kilovolt power
transmission plant recently became operational in the city of
Maoming, a major fruit producer and mining center in the western
part of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the plant, which cover 14 hectares, began in
September 1997. With an investment of 1.4 billion yuan, the plant
is expected to ease local power flow and stimulate economic growth.
The new power line is now part of the provincial power grid.
</P>
<P>
The western part of Guangdong is a relatively less developed
part of the province, which has witnessed one of the fast-paced
economic growth in China. The new facility is the largest power
plant in the province's western region. 
