<HEADLINE> French Household Confidence Continues to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The confidence of French households
continued to rise in July over June, said a major indicator of the
French National Institute of Economics and Statistics Study (INSEE)
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Summarized Indicator of Opinions of Households found that
the household confidence level stood at minus 8 in July, higher
than the minus 10 in April, May and June.
</P>
<P>
The highest point attained by the indicator of household
confidence in history was minus 7, in February 1987.
</P>
<P>
The result of comparison of household opinions about the level
of life of the past and future between July and the previous
months was also good, said INSEE.
</P>
<P>
Car sales in France increased by 22.5 percent in July over the
same month in 1998 to attain 292,701 units, in a growth for 21
consecutive months.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment rate dropped by 0.6 percent, or 18,000 people,
last month. 
</P>
