<HEADLINE> Nigeria May Deploy Troops to Combat Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Indications to this emerged Tuesday as the police redeployed
its commissioners, assistant commissioners, chief superintendent
and 105 other officers in an apparent attempt to curb the
increasing violent crimes, This Day paper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The government is said to believe that the crime wave which has
seen prominent citizens like renowned industrialist Chris
Ogunbajo, presidential adviser Alhaji Mahmud Wazri, former Sports
Minister Anthony Ikhazobh and others becoming victims, can no
longer be managed by ordinary policing methods.
</P>
<P>
