President Olusegun Obasanjo may have been seriously considering
the option of bringing in the troops at least temporarily, at the
request of some state governors with whom he extensively spoke on
telephone.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the National Security Council will also discuss
the activity of armed bandits in the north-south and northwest who
launch cross border raids into Nigeria maiming and killing
villagers in those areas.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the activities of menacing secret cults who
recently killed four students of the Obafemi Awolowo University at
Ile Ife would also be discussed by the council. 
