<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Explore New Sectors to Overcome Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia must go into new
sectors in order to overcome the economic crisis, Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
New sectors which could contribute to economic growth must be
identified and explored, he said here when launching the Second
National Economic Consultative Council (NECC II), a new council to
formulate new development policy for the first decade of the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
He said that for example, information technology (IT) could be
used to develop new IT based industries.
</P>
<P>
The country's Multimedia Super Corridor offers great potential
and training in this sector must be enhanced, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said an industry based on composite materials, which
are increasingly being used in automobiles and aircraft, could
contribute to the manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
He said the agriculture sector needed a new development
approach such as introducing large-scale estate management methods
in vegetable, fruit production and fish farming and adopting new
fishing techniques.
</P>
<P>
"The agriculture industry could be developed further with this
approach, not only in reducing food imports but also to export
surplus produce," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the agriculture sector had previously not been given
much attention as the country focused on developing the
manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The NECC II launched Wednesday will formulate proposals for a
new development policy which will guide the country's development
after the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
It will also look at strategies and targets on income
distribution, restructuring of human resources, shareholding and
taking into consideration macroeconomic factors, the main economic
sectors and foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
The NECC II has 155 members drawn from political parties,
chambers of commerce, professional bodies, industry and business
associations, non-governmental organizations, minority groups,
youths, women and selected individuals.
</P>
<P>
The council has to complete its task by August next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
