</P>
<P>
-- Europe is expected to be at the head of global economic
growth in the year 2000 with an envisaged rate of expansion
between 3 and 4 percent in the euro zone. In France, the sales of
new cars increased by a record 25 percent in July over one year
ago, while Germany is expected to have a 3 percent economic growth
this year. Spain's unemployment has also dropped to the lowest
since 1981 due to a sustained growth.
</P>
<P>
-- The French government has closed eight camps for young
scouts out of precaution against risks for the children, one year
after the accident in Perros-Guirec in the French Alps, in which
several scouts were killed during a mountain rambling. The
government has also warned parents against those associations
