<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Issues Writ of Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong has issued a writ of election, announcing August 18,
1999 as nomination day and August 28 as polling day for
presidential election, according to a press release from the Prime
Minister's Office Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The writ says polling day will be public holiday and voting is
compulsory.
</P>
<P>
The writ also says each candidate should pay 30,000 Singapore
dollars for deposit and candidates have to apply for a Certificate
of Eligibility before the end of August 7.
</P>
<P>
According to the writ, the Certificate of Eligibility shall
certify that the Presidential Election Committee is satisfied that
the person applying to contest the election is a person of
integrity, good character and reputation and the committee is of
the opinion that the person has such experience and ability in
administering and managing the financial affairs so as to enable
him to carry out effectively the functions and duties of the
office of president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
