<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 11 in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded in Northern
Province of Sri Lanka Wednesday noon killing at least 11 people
and injuring 21 others, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said the bombing was the work of the Tamil
rebels.
</P>
<P>
A woman suicide bomber strapped with explosives detonated the
device against the police Special Task Force (STF) truck at
Veppankulam in Vavuniya district, 344 Kilometers from Colombo, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The truck carrying about 30 STF commandos was traveling on the
Vavuniya-Mannar road around noon when the suicide bomber struck.
</P>
<P>
At least 10 police commandos and one civilian were killed and
21 others injured in the blast.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels were blamed for a similar suicide bombing
against a Tamil lawmaker while his car was stuck in a traffic jam
in Colombo last week.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 16--year-old war against
the government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of
the country. About 550,000 people have been killed in the war.
</P>
</TEXT>
