<HEADLINE> Lao-American MIA Technical Consultation Held in Vientiane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A technical consultation on
Lao-American cooperation in seeking for American soldiers missing
in action (MIA) in Laos during the Indochina War was held in Lao
capital Vientiane from Tuesday to Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, according to a report of Lao official news agency
KPL Wednesday, reviewed the Lao-American joint MIA operations and
bilateral cooperation in the first half of this year, and endorsed
a cooperation plan for the next six-month period.
</P>
<P>
Leading the Lao officials was Amphone Phithakphommachanh,
acting director of the Department of Europe-America in the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs, while the American side was headed by
Karen Stewart, charge d'affaires of the United States of America
to Laos.
</P>
<P>
Since the start of the Lao-American cooperation in 1980 there
have been 65 joint operations, with identification of 100 of the
500 reported cases.
</P>
<P>
A Lao spokesperson said that the Lao government has given
constant attention to the MIA affairs as a humanitarian matter
while the American people appreciate such cooperation. 
</P>
