<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Flat on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed flat on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as concerns about a tighter U.S.
interest policy weighted on a thin market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index closed at 2,144 points in a
moderate trading, up 0.63 points over Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 250.09 million shares worth
399.99 million Singapore dollars (238.33 million U.S. dollars).
Falls outpaced rises by 244 to 74 with 126 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Strike, a new comer, topped the volume list with a turnover of
65.16 million shares. It was followed by Excel which had 27.86
million units done. SingTel was the next with 7.86 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA and SIA DBScw00 headed the ascent as they gained 60 cents
each to close at 15.80 and 9.60 Singapore dollars respectively.
SIA 200 climbed up 50 cents to finish at 15.80 Singapore dollars.
A total of six stocks, namely, Bukit Sem, C&AMP;C, DBS F, SIA F, SPH
100 and Venture picked up 20 cents each and they ended at 17.00,
9.60, 22.20, 16.40, 30.80 and 15.00 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and GE Life led losers of the day,
dropping 40 cents to close at 17.30 and 20.00 Singapore dollars.
OCBC F sank 30 cents to finish at 14.30 Singapore dollars. F&AMP;N and
PacCent retreated 20 cents to end at 6.65 and 5.60 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said concerns about possible U.S. interest rate hike
still dominated the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
They also said summer holidays in Europe and the U.S. also
seemed to have affected the turnover in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
But they noted a new comer, Strike Engineering, managed to make
a strong debut. 
</P>
</TEXT>
