<HEADLINE> Zambia Bank to Ensure Y2K Compliant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Zambia has said it is
closely monitoring the financial institutions and has put in
measures to ensure that all principal customers and suppliers of
services to such institutions are Y2K compliant.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail Wednesday quoted public relations director
Kabinga Panda of the central bank as saying that it is mandatory
for all commercial banks to include in their Y2K progress reports
the relationship they have with their major clients.
</P>
<P>
"We have system in place to monitor the 2000 millenium bug
problem and at the moment almost all commercial banks are
compliant," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said some commercial banks' major clients are Y2K compliant.
</P>
<P>
However, the central bank does not directly monitor the
commercial banks' major clients to ensure they are compliant, he
added.
</P>
<P>
A survey at some commercial banks' stands show that there could
be a problem with some giant clients since some may not be Y2K
compliant or may just fail to be compliant by the turn of the
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
