<HEADLINE> Jordan to Extradite Murder Suspect to Yemen: Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Jordan has agreed to extradite
within days a Yemeni national to Sanaa who shot and killed a
Yemeni diplomat in Amman in June.
</P>
<P>
On June 5, Ahmad Mohammad Saleh stormed into the Yemeni Embassy
premises, shooting and killing consul Mohammad hmoud Mashidi and
wounding his deputy Fuad Zihairi, the semi-official Jordan Times
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jordan agreed to extradite the suspect since he is a Yemeni
national and the murder took place in the embassy premises that is
considered Yemeni soil in international law, Jordanian officials
said.
</P>
<P>
The suspect was allegedly drunken when he stormed into the
Yemeni mission and shot the diplomats.
</P>
<P>
He has been under custody of Jordanian police since the
shooting incident.
</P>
<P>
Sanaa has sought to get the suspect back for trial and Amman
responded positively to the request, Jordan Times said.
</P>
<P>
Both Jordan and Yemen are signatories to security-related and
anti-terrorist agreements under the umbrella of the Arab
League. 
</P>
</TEXT>
