<HEADLINE> Share Prices Tumble in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices plunged in Tokyo
Wednesday as high-tech blue chips were sold actively amid
expectation that the dollar would remain weak.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 284.55 points, or 1.58
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 17,685.38.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all First
Section issues dropped 22.32 points or 1.51 percent to 1,459.67.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to an estimated 472.32
million shares from Tuesday's 490.5 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Fujitsu was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei index opened higher but gradually slid as investors
took a wait-and-see attitude due to a lack of fresh incentives,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
The expectation that the dollar's weakness against the yen
would continue also helped to push share prices down, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 839 to 361, with 116 shares remaining unchanged. 
