<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Foreign Trade of China's Major Bonded Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and
figures about the foreign trade of China's major bonded zones (BZ)
between January and June this year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Port BZ reported a total trade volume of 368.813
million US dollars, up 10.9 percent from the same period last year.
Its exports reached 110.932 million US dollars, down 3.9 percent,
and imports reached 257.88 million US dollars, up 18.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Waigaoqiao BZ reported a foreign trade turnover of
2.099 billion US dollars, up 80 percent. Its exports surged 115.4
percent to 774.598 million, while imports grew 64.2 percent to 1.
324 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Futian Shatoujiao BZ of Shenzhen city, south China's
Guangdong Province, reported a foreign trade volume of 1.328
billion US dollars, up 16 percent. Its exports was recorded at 658.
253 million US dollars, up 25.2 percent. Its imports climbed 8.1
percent to 670.160 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Beilun Port BZ of Ningbo city, east China's Zhejiang
Province, reported a foreign trade turnover of 229.247 million US
dollars, down 11.6 percent. While exports of the BZ climbed 33.5
percent to 125.199 million, imports plummeted 37.1 percent to 104.
048 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Dayaowan BZ of Dalian city, northeast China's Liaoning
Province, reported a foreign trade turnover of 171.007 million US
dollars, down 10 percent. The BZ's exports dropped 3 percent to 90.
887 million and imports declined 16.7 percent to 80.119 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou BZ, south China's Guangdong Province, reported a
foreign trade turnover of 121.191 million US dollars, down 20.4
percent. While exports of the BZ reached 37.127 million US dollars,
down 46.3 percent, imports of the BZ climbed 1.1 percent to 84.064
million US dollars. 
</P>
