<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: China's Foreign Trade by Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and
figures about China's foreign trade for the first six months this
year, provided by the General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
January: exports at 11.389 million US dollars, down 10.9
percent from the same month last year; imports at 9.896 million US
dollars, up 13.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
February: exports at 10.999 million US dollars, down 10.2
percent; imports at 8.714 million US dollars, down 4.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
March: exports at 14.831 million US dollars, down 3.9 percent;
imports at 14.374 million US dollars, up 22.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
April: exports at 14.801 million US dollars, down 7.3 percent;
imports at 13.834 million US dollars, up 18.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
May: exports at 15.532 million US dollars, up 4.2 percent;
imports at 13.657 million US dollars, up 21.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
June: exports at 15.398 million US dollars, down 1.7 percent;
imports at 14.523 million US dollars, up 22.7 percent. 
</P>
