<HEADLINE> Sixty Overseas Chinese to Join Arctic Expedition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SNOW DRAGON SHIP, August 4 (Xinhua)-- The first Chinese Arctic
expedition will arrive at the Canadian port of Tuktoyaktuk on
August 13, where it will meet with another Arctic expedition team
made up of 60 overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The 60 overseas Chinese come from several countries, and they
were organized by a Canadian outdoor sports organization. the
leader of the Chinese Arctic Expedition Team, Chen Liqi, has
indicated that the 60 overseas Chinese will visit the Chinese
expedition's ship, the Snow Dragon, and take part in academic
exchanges with members of the expedition.
</P>
<P>
The expedition team is currently conducting oceanic,
atmospheric, and ice research at the Chukchi Sea, and will be in
port at Tuktoyaktuk for three days. Some members of the expedition
will be invited to the Canadian city of Inuvik to attend
receptions sponsored by the city government.
</P>
<P>
The 60 overseas Chinese intend to plant 180 trees within the
Arctic Circle to commemorate the expedition. 
