<HEADLINE> U.S. Commercial Library Opens in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States has opened up a
 commercial library in Kigali, capital of Rwanda, the Rwanda News
Agency (RNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The library which is to be located at the United States
Information Service (USIS) center will offer information about
various American products, manufacturers and investors for
business people in Rwanda to browse through the latest American
business magazines for new ideas and product information.
</P>
<P>
"It will also enable them to advertise their products and
investment opportunities to the American business community,"
official sources from the U.S. Embassy told the RNA.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the commercial library will be open to members
only with a membership fee of 30 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The library will have two internet terminals to connect the
members to a world of trade and commercial information with
assistance provided for those who are new to the worldwide web,"
said the sources. 
</P>
