<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Trade of China's Five Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and
figures about the foreign trade of China's five special economic
zones (SEZ) for the first six months this year, provided by the
General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 2.755
billion US dollars, down 10.3 percent from the same period last
year. Exports of the SEZ reached 1.531 billion US dollars, down 12.
4 percent, and imports of the SEZ dropped 7.7 percent to 1.225
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen SEZ reported a foreign trade turnover of 11.024
billion US dollars, up 11.8 percent. Exports of the SEZ was
recorded at 5.567 billion US dollars, down 0.9 percent, and
imports of the SEZ stood at 5.457 billion US dollars, up 28.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 2.382
billion US dollars, down 4 percent. Exports of the SEZ was
recorded at 1.006 billion US dollars, down 25.1 percent, and
imports of the SEZ stood at 1.377 billion US dollars, up 20.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shantou SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 1.29
billion US dollars, down 48.5 percent. Exports of the SEZ stood
at 508.656 million US dollars, down 64.8 percent, and imports of
the SEZ at 781.396 million US dollars, down 26.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province SEZ reported a total foreign trade volume of
563.605 million US dollars, down 31.7 percent. Exports of the SEZ
stood at 323.552 million US dollars, down 23.4 percent, and
imports of the SEZ at 240.053 million US dollars, down 40.4
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
