<HEADLINE> U.S. Biggest Trade Partner Of Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Trade between China's Shaanxi
Province and the United States was worth 118 million U.S. dollars
in the first half of this year, an increase of 31.9 percent over
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
It accounted for over 13 percent of Shaanxi's total foreign
trade for the period, making the United States the province's
biggest trade partner, according to the Xi'an Customs office.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi increased its imports from the United States by a big
margin during the period. It imported 44.66 million dollars worth
of equipment and electronic devices from the U.S., up 80 percent
from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
But, exports to the States dropped because of a significant
drop in Hong Kong's transit trade and provincial exports overall.
Shaanxi exports mainly textiles, medicines, glassware, machinery,
and garments to the States.
</P>
<P>
Its processing trade was worth 19.81 million dollars, down 27.8
percent, while general trade stood at 92.54 million dollars, up 61.
5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
