<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Courier, Lareau Win Second Round in Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- American Jim Courier eliminated
fourth-seeded Tim Henman of Britain 6-1, 6-7 (3-7), 6-4 in the
second round of the Canadian Open men's tennis tournament in
Montreal on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In another upset, Canadian Sebastien Lareau defeated fifth-
seeded Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands 4-6, 7-6 (7-4), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Henman edged Courier in five sets at Wimbledon this year after
Courier ousted the Briton in five sets in Birmingham, England.
This is Courier's third win in four career matches against Henman.
</P>
<P>
Henman is ranked fifth in the world while Courier, a four-time
Grand Slam winner who has slipped in the rankings, is No. 46.
</P>
<P>
Courier, punishing Henman from the baseline, had little trouble
in the first set. But Henman slowly gained momentum on his serve
and forced a second set tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
The top-ranked British player won the last four points to win 7-
3.
</P>
<P>
The two players were then on serve in the final set until
Courier broke Henman in the 10th game.
</P>
<P>
Henman has lost both his matches since making it to the semi-
finals at Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
Lareau, 26, ranked 116th in the world, played a solid first set,
losing on only one service break. In the second set, the players
were on serve when the match was halted briefly by rain. Lareau
came back to win the set in the tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
In the third set, Lareau saved two break points in the fourth
game and three more in the eighth before breaking the Dutchman.
</P>
<P>
It was Lareau's third win over a top 10 player, after beating
Michael Stich in 1994 and Alex Corretja last year.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, 13th-seeded Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia was
knocked out by Zimbabwean Byron Black 6-4, 6-4 in first-round
action.
</P>
<P>
Wayne Ferreira of South Africa entered the second round with a
three-set win over Mark Woodforde. American Vincent Spadea beat
Dutch lefty Jan Siemerink 6-2, 6-2 to advance to the third round.
</P>
</TEXT>
