<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Expects To Maintain Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, which has
been in the forefront of China's reforms and opening up, expects
to maintain its economic growth momentum in the later half of the
year, according to Huang Weihong, the director of the Provincial
Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Huang told the 11th meeting of the Standing Committee of the
Ninth Guangdong Provincial People's Congress yesterday that the
province will have a GDP growth rate of well over 9 percent this
year.
</P>
<P>
He said the province had economic growth of 9.6 percent and a
GDP of 367.58 billion yuan from January to June and put 104.5
billion yuan into fixed assets during that period.
</P>
<P>
To reach this year's economic goals, the province will focus on
markets and increase domestic demand, urban and rural incomes, and
promote state-owned enterprise reforms, and improve the economic
order this year, Huang said.
</P>
<P>
He promised that exports of state-owned foreign trade companies
and overseas-financed businesses will be stable and that there
will be more support for private export companies and companies
starting new processing businesses abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
