<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Finishes Third in Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The United States overcame a
shorthanded deficit to edge Saudi Arabia 2-0 on Tuesday and
clinched the third place in the FIFA Confederations Cup soccer
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The victory capped a strong performance in the Cup by the U.S.
squad, which upset Germany 2-0 and came close to tying Brazil in a
1-0 narrow loss.
</P>
<P>
Paul Bravo opened the scoring for the United States in the 27th
minute and an unmarked Brian McBride clinched the victory in the
78th minute.
</P>
<P>
The United States were reduced to ten men in the second half
after Paraguayan referee Ubaldo Aquino sent off midfielder Matt
McKeon for a second yellow card.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's Abdullah Bin Shehan knocked a pass into the U.S.
goal with his arm at the 23 minute mark, and officials quickly
disallowed the goal. Though the Saudis had several shots on goal
during the rest of the match, most lacked force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
