<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E.Timor's Ballot Registration Period Extended to Aug. 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan has agreed on the recommendation from the U.N. Mission
in East Timor (UNAMET) to extend the autonomy ballot registration
period to enable eligible voters to come to registration centers.
</P>
<P>
UNAMET Chief Ian Martin told reporters in Dili, capital of East
Timor, Wednesday that the ballot registration period will extend
from August 4 to 6.
</P>
<P>
The registration period in 14 remote areas will be open until
Sunday (August 8), Martin was quoted by the Antara News Agency as
saying.
</P>
<P>
As of Tuesday, more than 393,000 East Timorese inside and
outside the territory had registered for the direct ballot.
</P>
<P>
The registration will be followed by an appraisal, the
campaigns, two-day cooling off, and the direct ballot on August
30. An estimated 400,000 East Timorese are expected to go to the
polls.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. is organizing a direct ballot in East Timor to enable
the East Timorese to accept or reject a wide-ranging autonomy
offered by the Indonesian government.
</P>
<P>
A rejection of the autonomy proposal will mean independence for
the former Portuguese colony.
</P>
<P>
East Timor was integrated into Indonesia in 1976 in a move
never recognized by the U.N. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
