<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 3 (Xinhua) -- World Cup holder Michele Bartoli
said on Tuesday a serious knee injury was taking longer than
expected to heal and he would miss the world road race cycling
championships in October.
</P>
<P>
Bartoli said: "My knee needs time. Despite my determination and
really, really strong desire to take part in the world road race
championships in October and win it, the doctors have made me
change my mind."
</P>
