<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Advances Overseas Processing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen City in south China's
Guangdong Province has been introducing measures to promote
development of the city's processing service for overseas
customers.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen City Association of Overseas Processing Businesses was
founded recently to help its members solve problems, explore
market and improve competitiveness. It will serve as a bridge
between government departments and its members, report
difficulties of its members to the city government and put forward
suggestions for improvement, said Qiu Qingfang, the president of
the association.
</P>
<P>
Overseas processing is an important part of the export-oriented
economy for Shenzhen, a leading exporter in China. It has about 9,
000 businesses in processing services for overseas clients, with
about one million employees and about 800 million U.S. dollars in
earnings annually.
</P>
<P>
The overseas processing businesses delivered 8.7 billion U.S.
dollars worth of export in 1998, accounting for 33 percent of the
city's total export.  
</P>
