<HEADLINE> Argentina's Fiscal Income Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's fiscal income
fell to 4.07 billion U.S. dollars in July, down 7.2 percent from
the same month last year, the Economic Ministry declared Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to official analyses, the drop is due to the economic
recession caused by the devaluation of Brazil's currency at the
beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
For the first seven months of this year, there was also a drop
of 5.1 percent in fiscal income compared with the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the drop in July's fiscal income was due to
the loss in the collection of the Value Added Tax (VAT), which
fell by 18.5 percent against the same month last year. 
</P>
