<DOCNO> XIE19990804.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Produces Over 3 Mln Barrels of Crude Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced 3.378 million
barrels of crude oil in the fiscal year 1998-99 which ended in
March, a reduction of 252,000 barrels as compared with the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures released by the country's
Central Statistical Organization, the output of natural gas was
1.724 billion cubic-meters in 1998-99, a drop of 74 million
cubic-meters as compared with the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of April this year, foreign investment in the oil
and gas sector coming from Australia, Britain, France, Indonesia,
Japan, Thailand and the United States had reached 2.3 billion U.S.
dollars in 46 projects, accounting for 32.39 percent of the 7.108
billion dollars' total foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Until now, Myanmar's crude oil and natural gas production is
still self-insufficient and the country has to import 280,000 to
300,000 tons of crude oil and 100,000 to 150,000 tons of diesel
oil annually, the official statistics show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
