<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Releases New Strain of Maize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- China has officially released the
first Quality Protein Maize (QPM) hybrid strain - Zhongdan 9409 - ,
declaring it a significant agricultural breakthrough that will
ease the country's increasing food demand in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The yield potential of the new QPM strain reaches about 11 tons
per hectare against the present average yield of 4.96 tons, today'
s China Daily quoted agricultural scientists responsible for the
research as saying.
</P>
<P>
"It performed very well in several experimental demonstrations
in Hebei, Shaanxi, Henan and Guizhou provinces," said Zhang Shihua,
head of the research team under the Chinese Academy of
Agricultural Sciences (CAAS) during a news conference here hosted
by CAAS Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Maize is an important crop after rice and wheat in terms of
acreage but ranks second in terms of total production and yield in
China.
</P>
<P>
Yet, statistics provided by CAAS indicate that as the need and
consumption for animal protein increase rapidly in China, it is
expected that the demand for maize, which is used to feed
livestock, will also increase.
</P>
<P>
QPM maize has been considered an excellent option for such
strategic goals since its utilization efficiency in feeding pigs
and other livestock is 30 percent better than normal maize.
</P>
<P>
China embarked on QPM research in the mid-1970s at CAAS and
nine provincial research centers. The planting area of these QPM
hybrids has been extended to 334,000 hectares in total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990804.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Constructs Regional Industrial Parks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
spent 3.2 million U.S. dollars on infrastructure development of
regional industrial parks with a view to reducing unemployment at
regional level, Industrial Development Ministry sources said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, 5,000 jobs had been provided in 32 factories
which are in commercial operation in 14 industrial parks in the
country, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Once these factories are in full operation direct employment
opportunities would be available for 19,500 persons.
</P>
<P>
The government aims to develop infrastructure facilities in
these parks to reduce the upfront costs of investors, the sources
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that the government's industrial policy was
based on a multi-pronged strategy which features the promotion of
export-led industries, provision of a comprehensive network of
infrastructure facilities and the building up of multiple linkages
to rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
