<HEADLINE> Tiananmen Square Restoration Project Gets Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The face-lift of Beijing's Tian'
anmen Square has been given the High Quality Project award by the
Beijing Municipal People's Government.
</P>
<P>
The renovation project started last October and was completed
this June. The grounds were improved, high-density spotlights
installed, and major buildings cleaned.
</P>
<P>
The square was inspected 58 times to guarantee the quality of
the project, sources say. The renovation was the second in the
square's history and was done to mark the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
A panel gave a score of 96.74 points to the project, which is
expected to receive a national award next year.  
</P>
