<HEADLINE> Brazil's Beef Export Increases Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazil exported 25,1572
tons of beef in the first half of this year, jumping 45 percent
compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The country's Meat Industrial Exporters Association said
Tuesday that beef exports amounted to 367.3 million U.S. dollars,
up 38 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
President of the association Antonio Russo Neto attributed the
surge to the devaluation of the real which raised the
competitiveness of Brazil's beef exports, as well as to the
efforts Brazil has made to boost beef export. 
