<HEADLINE> Nott Becomes First Pan Am Women's Weightlifting Champion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 3 (Xinhua) -- American Tara Nott
became the first women's weightlifting champion in the history of
the Pan Am Games here today following her triumph in the 48kg
category on the first day of the competitions.
</P>
<P>
The American national champion snatched 77.5kgs and jerked
100kgs for a combined result of 177.5kgs, inking her name in the
48-year-old Pan Am Games record book.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old versatile athlete had played first division
soccer throughout college and on three US Olympic Festival Teams
before making her weightlifting debut in the national championship
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 56kg class event, Cuba's S. Alvarez Boulet lifted
115kgs in the snatch and 150kgs in the clean and jerk to make a
total of 265kgs, securing the gold medal with Colombia's N. Castro
Velasquez the silver with a combined lift of 255kgs.
</P>
<P>
Cuba triumphed again in tonight's last weightlifting event,
with W. Vargas Trujillo snatching 130kgs and jerking 155kgs for a
cumulative result of 285kgs to capture the men's 62kg gold.
</P>
</TEXT>
