<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Collection Of Songs From China's Xinjiang Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A collection of 1,898 folk songs
from the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, northwest China, will
be published this year, accordiong to the Xinjiang's Art Research
Institute.
</P>
<P>
The songs were collected from 12 ethnic groups who have lived
there for many generations. The Uygurs provided 490 folk songs,
the largest of all the ethnic groups. They are followed by the
Kazaks with 320 songs.
</P>
<P>
The is the largest collection of songs in one volume ever made
in Xinjiang. Many of them have become quite popular in China, such
as "The Girls in Daban Town", and "Song For A Toast". They reflect
almost all aspects of the life of people in Xinjiang and the
achievements of several generations of local artists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
