<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Foreign Debt Rises to 16.15 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's external debt reached 16.
15 billion U.S. dollars, the Finance Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 30 percent is owed to the World Bank, the Inter
American Development Bank, the Andean Promotion Corporation and
some other multilateral organizations.
</P>
<P>
