<HEADLINE> Panama's President Elect Announces Cabinet List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Panama's President-elect
Mireya Moscoso on Tuesday announced a list of 13 ministers making
up her government as of September 1.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet will be staffed by nine ministers from her
Arnulfista Party (PA) and four political allies with whom she will
form the head of the Panamanian Union (UP).
</P>
<P>
The designated ministers are: Foreign Affairs, Jose Miguel
Aleman; Finance and Treasury, Victor Juliao; Interior and Justice,
Winston Spadafora; Education, Dora Rosas; Public Works, Moises
Castillo; Presidency, Ivonn Young; Public Health, Jose Manuel
Teran; Labor, Joaquin Vallarino; Commerce and Industry, Joaquin
Jacome; Housing, Miguel Cardenas; Agricultural Development,
Alejandro Posse; Canal Affairs, Ricardo Martinelli; Women,
Children and Family, Alba Tejada.
</P>
<P>
Moscoso, who won the election on May 2, said during the
presentation of the ministers that her government would fight
against poverty and promote sustainable political development in
favor of all Panamanians.
</P>
<P>
The president elect noted that her government, made up of a
wide political alliance, would have to perform a huge range of
activities to fulfill its objectives.
</P>
<P>
"It is our opinion that the management of the coalition union
of Panama is characterized by the honesty, efficiency and
productivity of its members, in a way by which state resources
will be used rationally," she said.
</P>
<P>
Among the challenges Moscoso will have to face are fragile
social stability and strong political opposition led by the
Democratic Revolutionary Party (PRD), which will comprise a
majority in the next legislative assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
