<HEADLINE> Thailand, Vietnam to Promote Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Thai cabinet endorsed a proposal
on Tuesday to strengthen economic cooperation between Thailand and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The proposal, raised by the Joint Committee between Thailand
and Vietnam on Economic Cooperation, urged both parties to promote
trade by eliminating trade barriers as much as possible.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is requested in the proposal to invest more in
agro-industry in Vietnam while Vietnam is urged to export
petroleum and natural gas to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet agreed that both countries should organize trade
fairs, exchange trade delegations and hold meetings between
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
It agreed that the two countries should cooperate on 10
academic projects, such as education, agriculture, science and
technological development.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet also approved construction of a new highway
linking the two countries to promote transportation, trade and
tourism between them.
</P>
<P>
It also consented to arrange further meeting to finalize the
sea-natural resources research cooperation project between the two
sides. 
</P>
