<HEADLINE> Turkey's Leader to Visit U.S. in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister
Bulent Ecevit will visit the United States in September, the
White House announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit will meet President Bill Clinton to discuss Turkey's
longstanding dispute with Greece over the island of Cyprus,
National Security Council spokesman David Leavy said.
</P>
<P>
"Resolving Cyprus is a key priority for the administration,"
Leavy said.
</P>
<P>
Leavy said that the United States was encouraged by both
sides's willingness to hold negotiations on the dispute this
fall.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit's visit on Sept. 28 follows a trip to Turkey last
month by Defense Secretary William Cohen. 
</P>
